Arcane Signet is the biggest ham-fisted move Wizards has pulled in a while, but honestly for Brawl it's great and was pretty much necessary. Maybe they could have powered it down a bit (CIP tapped, life loss when you use it, etc), but it still would have probably been good enough to see Commander play and would have been expensive in the short term.
That's what boggles my mind a bit here, though... Arcane Signet is an absolutely **horrible** investment
So why are people buying into it so hard?
It is guaranteed to go down in price, so unless you time the market just right there's really no reason to be buying it right now other than cEDH.

As for the EDH players are buying out Brawl decks, that's true... but I think that's very common knowledge, and will not be the only criteria they use as to whether or not to keep on with the Brawl precons.
That’s... not a cEDH card...
Well then I stand corrected. Absolutely no one should be buying them.
But people are impatient, so what are you gonna do, I suppose.

I’m just gonna leave it at “I disagree.” I don’t think it was necessary, I agree it was designed by people who don’t understand Commander, etc. It may dip in price with future printings but so does Path to Exile. I don’t think I’m up for much talk about it beyond that. I disagree with the assessment.
I was initially on the side of defending Arcane Signet, but now I think I'd rather ruin an actual signet. So I guess now I'm just indifferent.

text: I don't do proxies in any fashion. I don't really like it. So I'll just not have one.
I get proxying a card you want to get but I really struggle with people who proxy readily available cards. Or people that proxy/fake a large portion of their deck and expect people to be ok with it
I personally don't like buying multiple of the same card, so I proxy, but for cards I own.
That might make me a cheapskate, but so be it.
collecting is a very important aspect to this game for me so i avoid proxying
my friend mark (some of yall met him at gpvegas) literally has 100% of his decks proxied typically

In general, I'm neither for or against proxies. I don't personally use them, nor do I run into many people who do... but for Arcane Signet specifically, I would argue that it's the right choice if you are going to insist on playing it in the short term.
he even proxies basics so the cards are the same thickness
I would also argue that it is no way necessary. You've lived this long without another signet, and it's not going to make even a percentage point of difference, so eh.
But I'm obviously in the minority in that opinion.
That said, classy proxies do go a long way. We've got a couple folks out my way with the printer for it, and it can be a lot of fun to see the results.
Dont care about proxying one way or another. Do have an issue with people proxying to up the power level beyond the playgroup though. But that's an issue more of power level then proxying
